Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Toss @butternut squash{12%ounce}(peeled and cubed) on a
#baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and a
pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Toss halfway through. After squash is done, preheat broiler to high or increase oven to 500 degrees.

Bring 1 cup water, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, and @quinoa{1/2%cup} to a boil in #small pot{}. Once boiling, cover and reduce to a low simmer until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1%unit}. Trim then halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} through stem, then thinly slice into shreds.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large #ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and toss until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add Brussels sprouts and toss until tender and lightly browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Remove pan from heat. Zest @lemon{1%unit}(zested) into pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halve lemon. Once quinoa and squash are ready, toss both into pan with Brussels sprouts. Add @pecans{1%ounce}, @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, a squeeze of lemon, a large drizzle of olive oil, and a generous pinch of salt and pepper.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture to a small baking dish.

Sprinkle quinoa mixture with @Gruyère cheese{1/2%cup}(shredded) and broil or bake until browned and melty, about ~{3%minutes}, and serve.